    <p>Honest opinion on this tier: a 13-year-old HR-Series with major compressor failure usually doesn't pencil out to repair. New HR2-1S landed runs roughly $4,500 to $5,500 commercial wholesale. A $2,200 compressor swap on a unit with a worn condenser, aged door gasket, and defrost timer drift you'll be replacing in 18 months anyway is throwing good money after bad. We tell operators that on the diagnostic call.</p>
